chunks.translated_text:
Transmit this to the late spring, then to the heart, spleen, lungs, kidneys, and liver, connecting them in due succession. For the late summer, transmit to the lungs, kidneys, liver, heart, and spleen, connecting them in due succession. For the late autumn, transmit to the kidneys, liver, heart, spleen, and lungs, connecting them in due succession. For the late winter, transmit to the liver, heart, spleen, lungs, and kidneys, connecting them in due succession.

Another method: For late autumn and late winter, employ warmth, harmony, and pure concentration. For spring and summer, the terms "warmth and harmony" are not required.

Next, invoke the deities of the four seasons:
In spring, invoke the Four Departments’ Radiant Lord;
In summer, the Supreme Tenuity Jade Flower Lord;
In autumn, the Lesser Brilliance Golden Portal Jade Gate Lord;
In winter, the Great Obscurity Profound Darkness Lord.
For this year’s governing spirit, [name], with attendant officials numbering [count].
For this month’s governing spirit, [name], with attendant officials numbering [count].
For this day’s governing spirit, [name], with attendant officials numbering [count].
For this hour’s governing spirit, [name], with attendant officials numbering [count].

The yearly governing spirit is the Grand Year Spirit, which is this month’s governing spirit.
In years of *jia* and *ji*, the first month is established in *bing-yin*, the second in *ding-mao*, and so on through the twelve months; other years follow this pattern.
In years of *yi* and *geng*, the first month is established in *wu-yin*, the second in *ji-mao*.
In years of *bing* and *xin*, the first month is established in *geng-yin*.
In years of *ding* and *ren*, the first month is established in *ren-yin*.
In years of *wu* and *gui*, the first month is established in *jia-yin*.
By this method, the six *jia* of the month are known.

The day’s governing spirit is the day spirit of the preceding petition.
The hour’s governing spirit is also determined by the *jia* and *ji* cycle:
On *jia* and *ji* days, the first hour begins with *bing-yin*.
On *yi* and *geng* days, the first hour begins with *wu-yin*.
On *bing* and *xin* days, the first hour begins with *geng-yin*.
On *ding* and *ren* days, the first hour begins with *ren-yin*.
On *wu* and *gui* days, the first hour begins with *jia-yin*.
By this method, the six *jia* of the hour are known.

Next, according to the four seasons, transmit the petition to the Jade Lads and Jade Maidens:
In spring, to the Azure Jade Lad and Azure-Sashed Jade Maiden;
In summer, to the Vermilion Jade Lad and Vermilion Jade Maiden;
In autumn, to the White Jade Lad and White Jade Maiden;
In winter, to the Profound Simplicity Great Dawn Jade Lad and Mysterious Mechanism Jade Maiden.
Ensure it is conveyed upward to receive the profound grace.

Next, proceed to the Supreme [N.] Palace and await the report:
On the first day, the Jade Bureau’s Crimson Void Palace;
On the second, the Supreme Tenuity Bureau’s Supreme Tenuity Palace;
On the third, the Supreme Tenuity Bureau’s Northern Peace Palace;
On the fourth, the Capital Rectifier Bureau’s Supreme Clarity Palace;
On the fifth, the Orthodox Unity Bureau’s Illuminating Communication Palace;
On the sixth, the Profound Unity Bureau’s Upper Clarity Palace;
On the seventh, the Supreme Tenuity Bureau’s Lofty Spirit Palace;
On the eighth, the Spirit Assembly Bureau’s Purple Tenuity Palace;
On the ninth, the Cinnabar Spirit Bureau’s Awaiting Spring Palace;
On the tenth, the Supreme Clarity Bureau’s Martial Spirit Palace;
On the eleventh, the Three Waters Bureau’s White Maiden Palace;
On the twelfth, the Registrar Bureau’s Vast Plain Palace;
On the thirteenth, the Pure Uncle Bureau’s Western Clarity Palace;
On the fourteenth, the Profound Rectifier Bureau’s Upper Crimson Palace;
On the fifteenth, the Central Capital Bureau’s Crooked Peace Palace;
On the sixteenth, the Censor Bureau’s Northern Mansion Palace;
On the seventeenth, the Surveillance Bureau’s Southern Perfection Palace;
On the eighteenth, the Governing Bureau’s Eastern Clarity Palace;
On the nineteenth, the Governing Registrar Bureau’s Western Spirit Palace;
On the twentieth, the Inspector Bureau’s Controller of Destiny Palace;
On the twenty-first, the Supervisor Bureau’s Yang Brilliance Palace;
On the twenty-second, the Examiner Bureau’s Great Yang Palace;
On the twenty-third, the Palace Bureau’s Lesser Yang Palace;
On the twenty-fourth, the Profound Heaven Bureau’s Great Yin Palace;
On the twenty-fifth, the Supreme Profundity Bureau’s Lesser Yin Palace;
On the twenty-sixth, the Capital Controller Bureau’s Northern Culmen Palace;
On the twenty-seventh, the Capital Observer Bureau’s Grand White Palace;
On the twenty-eighth, the Directing Envoy Bureau’s Forest Clarity Palace;
On the twenty-ninth, the Controller Bureau’s All Yangs Palace;
On the thirtieth, the Examiner Bureau’s Radiant Dawn Palace.

These are the thirty palace bureaus of a single month; the petition day follows this order.

If the petition is to be presented to the monthly palace, record the following at the end of the scroll:
In the first month, the Supreme Void Venerable’s Palace;
In the second, the Supreme Profound Elder’s Immortal Capital Palace;
In the third and fourth, the Supreme Three Heavens’ Supreme Clarity Palace;
In the fifth, the Supreme Dao Spirit Palace (also called the Double Dao Palace);
In the sixth and seventh, the Supreme Nine *Qi* Literary Prosperity Palace;
In the eighth, the Supreme Heavenly Thearch’s Palace;
In the ninth and tenth, the Supreme Great Dao Palace;
In the eleventh, the Supreme Attendant Left and Right Supervising Spirit Generals’ Palace;
In the twelfth, the Supreme Void Venerable’s Palace (same as the first month).
In an intercalary month, the Supreme Golden Simplicity Grand Year Palace.

The *Yuanchen* Petition and Offering Established Calendar, Scroll the Lower, is now complete.
